	<li>
		<div>
				<author-avatar data-url="/resources/images/article_assets/2013/09/110-vijay-govindarajan.jpg" data-author-name="Vijay Govindarajan" data-js-target="author-avatar" style="background-image: url(/resources/images/article_assets/2013/09/110-vijay-govindarajan.jpg);">
				</author-avatar>
		</div>
		<div>
					<span>
						<a href="/search?term=vijay%20govindarajan&search_type=search-all">Vijay Govindarajan</a>&#160;is the Coxe Distinguished Professor at Dartmouth College&#8217;s Tuck School of Business and faculty partner at the Silicon Valley incubator&#160;<a href="https://www.mach49.com/the-team">Mach 49</a>. He is a&#160;<em>New York Times</em>&#160;and&#160;<em>Wall Street Journal</em>&#160;bestselling author. His latest book is&#160;<a href="http://www.3boxsolution.com/"><em>The Three Box Solution</em></a>. His&#160;Harvard Business Review&#160;articles &#8220;<a href="https://hbr.org/2015/07/engineering-reverse-innovations">Engineering Reverse Innovations</a>&#8221; and &#8220;<a href="https://hbr.org/2010/07/stop-the-innovation-wars">Stop the Innovation Wars</a>&#8221; won McKinsey Awards for best article published in HBR. His&#160;HBR&#160;articles &#8220;<a href="https://hbr.org/2009/10/how-ge-is-disrupting-itself">How GE Is Disrupting Itself</a>&#8221; and &#8220;<a href="https://hbr.org/2011/01/the-ceos-role-in-business-model-reinvention">The CEO&#8217;s Role in Business Model Reinvention</a>&#8221; are&#160;HBR&#160;all-time top 50 bestsellers. Follow Vijay on&#160;<a href="https://twitter.com/vgovindarajan">Twitter</a>&#160;and&#160;<a href="https://twitter.com/vgovindarajan">LinkedIn</a>.
					</span>
		</div>
	</li>
	</ul>

